@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_NavigationReplacesEmbeddedSnapshot> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_NavigationReplacesEmbeddedSnapshot> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_NavigationReplacesEmbeddedSnapshot> ;
    narr:childCount "9"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "b6a9d4d918338cfce5a392033500736cbdfb157d" ;
    narr:narration """The core move, established 2026-06-16, is that no consumer receives a pre-fetched blob: every agent and every human reads through the digest and navigates from there. [Navigation dropping context by an order of magnitude](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_NavigationDropsContextOrderOfMagnitude) was both the fix for flakiness and the architectural direction — one decision. [Extraction roaming without pre-scoped focus](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ExtractionRoamsNoPreScope) follows directly: a memory can touch pricing, positioning, and a person at once, and pre-choosing a focus would blind the agent to two of them. [Steering guidance placed in the returned surface rather than each caller's prompt](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_GuidanceInSurfaceNotPrompt) proved the principle — cite and introspect needed zero prompt changes. By 2026-06-30, [a consultant who ran enterprise discovery engagements for fifteen years's independent HATEOAS/RFC 8288 framing](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_DiscoveryConsultantHATEOASParallel) converged on the same traverse-don't-big-query instinct from a linked-data layer. By 2026-07-01 the pattern had propagated into structure: [perspective responses ordered by volatility](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_PerspectiveResponseOrderedByVolatility) with a stable map leading and per-call focus appended last; [synchronous per-message integration](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SynchronousPerMessageIntegration) to prevent drift; and [the digest browser as the human-facing product surface](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DigestBrowserProductSurface) — the human as consumer of the same collapse/expand path agents already use. The [content/commentary split](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ContentCommentarySplit) sits adjacent: read-model implemented, write practice not yet.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ExtractionRoamsNoPreScope> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_GuidanceInSurfaceNotPrompt> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_DiscoveryConsultantHATEOASParallel> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_NavigationDropsContextOrderOfMagnitude> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ProxyReasonsNotPreFetches> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ContentCommentarySplit> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DigestBrowserProductSurface> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_PerspectiveResponseOrderedByVolatility> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SynchronousPerMessageIntegration> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The compiled snapshot had grown to roughly half a million tokens. The fix for the flakiness and the direction of the architecture were one decision." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_NavigationDropsContextOrderOfMagnitude> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "cite and introspect navigated correctly with zero changes to their skills, purely off the tool descriptions and the collapsed return — the proof of the principle." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_GuidanceInSurfaceNotPrompt> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "traversing a graph rather than asking big SPARQL queries of it." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_DiscoveryConsultantHATEOASParallel> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "every traversal in your world is a very small operation; in my world it's actually a network call" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_DiscoveryConsultantHATEOASParallel> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "it grounds answers as it forms them, reasoning after each step, rather than fetching a context blob up front." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ProxyReasonsNotPreFetches> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The map is never reordered per call. Focus selects what to append, never what to move." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_PerspectiveResponseOrderedByVolatility> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "async creates drift between the individual and the actual experience of the individual." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SynchronousPerMessageIntegration> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "This is a write primitive that is read-implemented but not yet written." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ContentCommentarySplit> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Full agent restructure chosen over a lighter one-shot navigate-to-context step for the Front Q&A surface — the gain is after-each-step grounding, the cost is a larger change to a customer-facing product." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ProxyReasonsNotPreFetches> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "a consultant who ran enterprise discovery engagements for fifteen years's HATEOAS framing agrees on traverse-don't-big-query but marks a real layer difference: in-process traversal is cheap; his equivalent is a network call per hop, making the cost structure meaningfully different even if the instinct is the same." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_DiscoveryConsultantHATEOASParallel> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Synchronous per-message integration is the stated default, but MCP clients cannot be forced to call a tool every message — a hybrid model may be required there, leaving the sync guarantee conditional on the integration surface." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SynchronousPerMessageIntegration> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The content/commentary split is read-implemented but not yet write-implemented — the design is settled in the read model while the write practice lags, an open asymmetry." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ContentCommentarySplit> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}